{"key":"post-10484999","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10484999</id>\n<content>I would not put the blower in the box.&amp;nbsp; I've seen that design before and it never seems to accomplish laminar flow unless you extend the box above the filter, but then the damn thing weighs a ton and is hard to move.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You want a steady even pressure all across the back side of the filter.&amp;nbsp; That is how you get an even airspeed leaving the front side, which is required for laminar flow.&amp;nbsp; Most true HEPA filters are 5 1/2 to 11 inches thick.&amp;nbsp; I'd try to have that much unobstructed space directly behind the filter.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10485083</next>\n<prev>10484982</prev>\n<first>10471855</first>\n<last>10491595</last>\n<when>1244688620</when>\n<utime>06/11/09 05:50 AM</utime>\n</post>"}